{"DESPAIR":[{"def":"To be hopeless; to have no hope; to give up all hope or expectation; -- often with of.","pos":""}],"DESPAIRER":[{"def":"One who despairs.","pos":""}],"DESPAIRING":[{"def":"Feeling or expressing despair; hopeless.","pos":""}],"DESPARPLE":[{"def":"To scatter; to disparkle.","pos":""}],"DESPATCH":[{"def":"Same as Dispatch.","pos":""}],"DESPECIFICATE":[{"def":"To discriminate; to separate according to specific signification or qualities; to specificate; to desynonymize.","pos":""}],"DESPECIFICATION":[{"def":"De*spec`ifi*ca\"tion, n.","pos":""}],"DESPECTION":[{"def":"A looking down; a despising.","pos":""}],"DESPEED":[{"def":"To send hastily.","pos":""}],"DESPEND":[{"def":"To spend; to squander.","pos":""}],"DESPERADO":[{"def":"A reckless, furious man; a person urged by furious passions, and regardless of consequence; a wild ruffian.","pos":""}],"DESPERATE":[{"def":"Without hope; given to despair; hopeless.","pos":""},{"def":"Beyond hope; causing despair; extremely perilous; irretrievable; past cure, or, at least, extremely dangerous; as, a desperate disease; desperate fortune.","pos":""}],"DESPERATELY":[{"def":"In a desperate manner; without regard to danger or safety; recklessly; extremely; as, the troops fought desperately.","pos":""}],"DESPERATENESS":[{"def":"Desperation; virulence.","pos":""}],"DESPERATION":[{"def":"The act of despairing or becoming desperate; a giving up of hope.","pos":""},{"def":"A state of despair, or utter hopeless; abandonment of hope; extreme recklessness; reckless fury.","pos":""}],"DESPICABILITY":[{"def":"Des`pi*ca*bil\"i*ty, n.","pos":""}],"DESPICABLE":[{"def":"Fit or deserving to be despised; contemptible; mean; vile; worthless; as, a despicable man; despicable company; a despicable gift.","pos":""}],"DESPICABLENESS":[{"def":"The quality of being despicable; meanness; vileness; worthlessness.","pos":""}],"DESPICABLY":[{"def":"In a despicable or mean manner; contemptibly; as, despicably stingy.","pos":""}],"DESPICIENCY":[{"def":"A looking down; despection.","pos":""}],"DESPISABLE":[{"def":"Despicable; contemptible.","pos":""}],"DESPISAL":[{"def":"A despising; contempt.","pos":""}],"DESPISE":[{"def":"To look down upon with disfavor or contempt; to contemn; to scorn; to disdain; to have a low opinion or contemptuous dislike of.","pos":""}],"DESPISEDNESS":[{"def":"The state of being despised.","pos":""}],"DESPISER":[{"def":"One who despises; a contemner; a scorner.","pos":""}],"DESPITE":[{"def":"Malice; malignity; spite; malicious anger; contemptuous hate.","pos":""},{"def":"An act of malice, hatred, or defiance; contemptuous defiance; a deed of contempt.","pos":""}],"DESPITEFUL":[{"def":"Full of despite; expressing malice or contemptuous hate; malicious.","pos":""}],"DESPITEOUS":[{"def":"Feeling or showing despite; malicious; angry to excess; cruel; contemptuous.","pos":""}],"DESPITEOUSLY":[{"def":"Des*pit\"e*ous*ly, adv.","pos":""}],"DESPITOUS":[{"def":"Despiteous; very angry; cruel.","pos":""}],"DESPOIL":[{"def":"To strip, as of clothing; to divest or unclothe.","pos":""},{"def":"To deprive for spoil; to plunder; to rob; to pillage; to strip; to divest; -- usually followed by of.","pos":""}],"DESPOILER":[{"def":"One who despoils.","pos":""}],"DESPOLIATION":[{"def":"A stripping or plundering; spoliation.","pos":""}],"DESPOND":[{"def":"To give up, the will, courage, or spirit; to be thoroughly disheartened; to lose all courage; to become dispirited or depressed; to take an unhopeful view.","pos":""}],"DESPONDENCE":[{"def":"The people, when once infected, lose their relish for happiness [and] saunter about with looks of despondence.","pos":""}],"DESPONDENCY":[{"def":"The state of desponding; loss of hope and cessation of effort; discouragement; depression or dejection of the mind.","pos":""}],"DESPONDENT":[{"def":"Marked by despondence; given to despondence; low-spirited; as, a despondent manner; a despondent prisoner.","pos":""}],"DESPONDER":[{"def":"One who desponds.","pos":""}],"DESPONDINGLY":[{"def":"In a desponding manner.","pos":""}],"DESPONSAGE":[{"def":"Athilrid, his daughter.","pos":""}],"DESPONSATION":[{"def":"A betrothing; betrothal.","pos":""}],"DESPONSORY":[{"def":"A written pledge of marriage.","pos":""}],"DESPOT":[{"def":"A master; a lord; especially, an absolute or irresponsible ruler or sovereign.","pos":""},{"def":"One who rules regardless of a constitution or laws; a tyrant.","pos":""}],"DESPOTAT":[{"def":"The station or government of a despot; also, the domain of a despot.","pos":""},{"def":"Having the character of, or pertaining to, a despot; absolute in power; possessing and abusing unlimited power; evincing despotism; tyrannical; arbitrary.","pos":""}],"DESPOTISM":[{"def":"The power, spirit, or principles of a despot; absolute control over others; tyrannical sway; tyranny.","pos":""},{"def":"A government which is directed by a despot; a despotic monarchy; absolutism; autocracy.","pos":""}],"DESPOTIST":[{"def":"A supporter of despotism.","pos":""}],"DESPOTIZE":[{"def":"To act the despot.","pos":""}],"DESPUMATE":[{"def":"To throw off impurities in spume; to work off in foam or scum; to foam.","pos":""}],"DESPUMATION":[{"def":"The act of throwing up froth or scum; separation of the scum or impurities from liquids; scumming; clarification.","pos":""}],"DESPUME":[{"def":"To free from spume or scum.","pos":""}]}